Package: SWCalibrateR
Version: 1.1.0
Date: 2019-03-19
Title: Flexible calibration tool for soil moisture sensors
Authors@R: c(
    person("Johannes", "Brenner", email = "johannes.brennner@ufz.de",
        role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Giulio", "Genova", email = "Giulio.Genova@eurac.edu",
        role = c("aut")))
Maintainer@R: person("Johannes", "Brenner", email = "johannes.brennner@ufz.de",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The R-shiny toolbox calibrates soil moisture sensors using volumetric
    water content (VWC) measured in-situ by soil moisture sensors and retrieved 
    from soil samples (field campaigns plus laboratory work). 
    It includes an interactive shiny app for data upload and 
    subset, estimation of linear models (OLS and robust MM-type estimator), 
    visualisation of data and model estimate as well as model diagnostics,
    in order to be able to identify leverage and outlier points.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
